/>=F0=9F=9A=A8 <i>Paramount=E2=80=99s biggest non-Redstone voting sharehold=
er files a major lawsuit</i>: <b>Mario Gabelli</b>, the long-suffering inve=
stor who has long been the largest of the non-<b>Redstone</b> Class A share=
holders in Paramount Global, has just filed suit in Delaware, seeking acces=
s to Paramount=E2=80=99s books and records. According to Gabelli, who calle=
d me on Friday afternoon to share the news, he isn=E2=80=99t
opposed to <b>Shari</b>=E2=80=99s deal to sell the company to the<b> Elliso=
ns</b> and RedBird Capital. He=E2=80=99s also perfectly fine, <i>in princip=
le</i>, with Shari getting a premium for her Class A shares. But he=E2=80=
=99s concerned about the allocation, noting that Shari has both A shares an=
d B shares, and wants to make sure she=E2=80=99s not getting more for her B=
 shares than others. =E2=80=9CI got to represent all investors here,=E2=80=
=9D he told me. Stay tuned=E2=80=A6 =E2=80=94<i>Eriq Gardner</i><br/><br/><=
i>And a few other notes from me=E2=80=A6</i><br/><br/>=F0=9F=93=BA <i>Hot B=
iden Summer</i>: In the wake of Thursday=E2=80=99s signs-of-life press conf=
erence, President <b>Biden</b> will follow up next week with not one but <i=
>three</i> national media appearances. The highly anticipated interview wit=
h NBC=E2=80=99s <b>Lester Holt</b>, on Monday, was announced earlier this w=
eek. But, as I <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6Im=
RnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dRcU51Y0RZZ1lvdXdqUFc5aVN1OD0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6L=
y94LmNvbS9keWxhbmJ5ZXJzL3N0YXR1cy8xODExNDg4MTczOTQxNDU3MTQzP3M9NDZcdTAwMjZ0=
PXVPYXBPaXFBdGFkZG03MXV5dC1GMUFcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249SW4rVGhlK1Jvb20rLSt=
TVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjg3JTJGMTIlMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PUluK1RoZStSb2=
9tKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4NiUyRjE0JTJGMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX=
