>scooped on X</a></u>, the president will also do interviews with a Black n=
ational media network on Tuesday and a Latino national media network on Wed=
nesday. So, not stepping aside just yet, anyway.<br/><br/>Obviously, for Bi=
den, the media has become the message: He simply needs to show voters (and =
lawmakers and donors and, yes, pundits) that he is capable of answering que=
stions on camera, fluidly, and without a teleprompter=E2=80=94a boon to the=
 news networks that have had such a hard time booking him over these last t=
hree and a half years. Indeed, NBC has <i>long </i>had a standing invitatio=
n to the president, and I=E2=80=99m told by sources at both 30 Rock and the=
 White House that this arrangement came together simply because the Biden t=
eam <i>finally</i> called and said, =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re
ready.=E2=80=9D Of course, at some point the president, if he stays in the =
race, will also need to use the medium to advance his <i>actual message</i>=
 and more effectively prosecute the case against <b>Trump</b>, not simply d=
emonstrate his cognizance.<br/><br/>=F0=9F=97=9E=EF=B8=8F <i>The Will Lewis=
 =E2=80=9CSwitch=E2=80=9D</i>: <b>Will Lewis</b>=E2=80=99s <i>Washington Po=
st</i> has unveiled a new marketing campaign that seeks to put a more posit=
ive spin on the ominous, <b>Woodward</b>- and <b>Baron</b>-conceived (and <=
b>Bezos</b>-approved) =E2=80=9CDemocracy Dies in Darkness=E2=80=9D slogan t=
he company has utilized since the early Trump era. In a memo to staff this =
week, chief strategy officer <b>Suzi Watford</b> announced an =E2=80=9Cacti=
ve, optimistic build=E2=80=9D on the old motto: Since =E2=80=9CDemocracy Di=
es in Darkness,=E2=80=9D she wrote, =E2=80=9Cwe say Switch On.=E2=80=9D <i>=
Get it?</i><br/><br/>It=E2=80=99s hard to tell if <i>Switch On </i>will <i>=
catch on</i>, but the <i>Post </i>will certainly make a go of it. As Semafo=
r recently reported, Lewis is
planning an aggressive new marketing campaign to help burnish the reputatio=
n of the beleaguered brand. I certainly think it=E2=80=99s an improvement, =
for whatever that=E2=80=99s worth. But as a more dubious digital media exec=
utive observed, it might also be premature: =E2=80=9CI have no idea if =E2=
=80=98Switch On=E2=80=99 is a good message or a bad message, but my instinc=
t is that it=E2=80=99s generic, forgettable, and scarce money down the drai=
n,=E2=80=9D this person said. =E2=80=9CUsually, marketing messages work bes=
t when you=E2=80=99ve got the goods. When you=E2=80=99ve done the work. Whe=
n you=E2=80=99re well differentiated. Heck, they don=E2=80=99t even have a =
permanent editor. They haven=E2=80=99t even stood up their =E2=80=98third n=
ewsroom.=E2=80=99 Why bother marketing the old product that hasn=E2=80=99t =
even really changed yet?=E2=80=9D<br/><br/><i>Now, back to the Duck Pond=E2=
=80=A6</i><br/></p>
