          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">The Allen &amp; Com=
pany Conference, <b>Herb Allen</b>=E2=80=99s annual high-altitude, midsumme=
r summit in Sun Valley, Idaho, for tech entrepreneurs, media chiefs, and ot=
her masters of the universe, is almost always an easygoing and amicable aff=
air. The sun shines; the aspens quake; the programming impresses=E2=80=94<b=
>Bill Gates </b>and <b>Jeff Bezos</b> shared the stage here on Friday=E2=80=
=94families are invited, and well cared for; recreational activities abound=
; dinners are relaxed; and above all else, attendees have ample time to mee=
t and scheme with one another, free from office retinues and buoyed by the =
pride of knowing that they are members of a <i>very </i>exclusive club of p=
eople with <i>real</i> power, money, and influence. <br/><br/>Alas, in the =
summer of a highly fraught presidential campaign season, even this idyllic =
retreat is not immune from the tensions
roiling the rest of society. And, at one point, things took a decidedly ten=
se and awkward turn when former Stanford classmates <b>Reid Hoffman </b>and=
 <b>Peter Thiel </b>began sparring over <b>Biden </b>and <b>Trump</b>, with=
 the entire conference looking on.<br/><br/>Of course, Hoffman and Thiel ha=
ve spent years on the opposite side of the political spectrum: Hoffman as a=
 major Democratic donor and Biden advocate; Thiel as an early Trump support=
er, albeit notably <i>not</i> a donor this time around. For years, the fell=
ow PayPal alumni fought and argued over politics but maintained their longt=
ime friendship=E2=80=94even during their 2022 proxy war in Ohio, where Thie=
l poured $15 million into groups backing <b>J.D. Vance</b>=E2=80=99s Senate=
 campaign, and Hoffman supported the Democrats in legislative and statewide=
 races. By the following year, however, their political disagreements had p=
ut a strain on the relationship. In an interview in March 2023, Hoffman tol=
d <b>Kara Swisher</b>,
=E2=80=9CPeter and I talk a lot less now than we used to=E2=80=94I mean<i> =
a lot</i> less=E2=80=94partially because if we=E2=80=99re going to talk, we=
=E2=80=99re going to argue about this. =E2=80=A6 It=E2=80=99s probably been=
 challenging for both of us.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>As their exchange here at th=
e conference made clear, it has indeed been <i>quite </i>challenging. On We=
dnesday morning, more than half a dozen conference attendees told me, Hoffm=
an was onstage with Palantir C.E.O. <b>Alex Karp </b>in conversation with m=
oderator <b>Andrew Ross Sorkin</b>. At one point, Sorkin asked Hoffman to t=
alk about his relationship with Thiel. Reid offered some kind words for his=
 former friend but said he doesn=E2=80=99t speak to him anymore because of =
his support for Trump, which Hoffman called =E2=80=9Ca moral issue.=E2=80=
=9D <br/><br/>Thiel, who was sitting in the audience along with all the oth=
er conference attendees, appeared to be visibly miffed over this accusation=
 of moral delinquency. He ultimately stood up for himself and offered his o=
wn
retort. As multiple attendees told me, Thiel told Hoffman that his door was=
 always open if he ever wanted to talk. He also sarcastically thanked him f=
or having sent him a deck of his =E2=80=9CTrumped Up Cards=E2=80=9D=E2=80=
=94the satirical anti-Trump, Cards Against Humanity-style deck Hoffman crea=
ted in 2016. =E2=80=9CI sent you the first deck, Peter,=E2=80=9D Hoffman re=
plied.<br/><br/>For a moment, some attendees said, it seemed as if the exch=
ange between the former friends might end amicably. Then Thiel got serious.=
 In 2016, the cards had been funny, he said, but a few months later, after =
Trump won the White House, they looked silly (Thiel donated $1.25 million t=
o Trump in that campaign). Thiel then intimated that Hoffman=E2=80=99s obse=
ssion with small-minded tactics was misguided, hadn=E2=80=99t worked in 201=
6, and wouldn=E2=80=99t work now=E2=80=94and, moreover, that all of Hoffman=
=E2=80=99s efforts to combat Trump only made him stronger. =E2=80=9CHe was =
aggressively and condescendingly glib,=E2=80=9D one attendee said. =E2=80=
=9CHe seemed to be
saying, =E2=80=98It doesn=E2=80=99t matter what you do. Bring it on.=E2=80=
=99=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Then, in what one source described as =E2=80=9Cthe da=
gger=E2=80=9D and another as a =E2=80=9Ctwist of the knife,=E2=80=9D Thiel =
sarcastically thanked Hoffman for funding lawsuits against Trump because th=
ey had turned him into =E2=80=9Ca martyr,=E2=80=9D thereby increasing his c=
hances of re-election. =E2=80=9CI am so grateful to you,=E2=80=9D Thiel sai=
d.<br/><br/>From the stage, Hoffman shot back with his own sarcastic quip: =
=E2=80=9CYeah, I wish I had made him an <i>actual</i> martyr.=E2=80=9D And,=
 on that very uncomfortable note, the exchange ended. (Both Hoffman and Thi=
el did not respond to emails requesting comment.) <br/><br/>The incident wa=
s a subject of much discussion at dinner that night, I=E2=80=99m told. Even=
 up until Friday, several conference attendees were still reflecting on the=
 surreal nature of what they=E2=80=99d witnessed. =E2=80=9CIt was <i>a thin=
g,</i>=E2=80=9D one told me. =E2=80=9CIt was <i>so </i>intense and so incre=
dibly weird=E2=80=94and just sad.=E2=80=9D As another attendee put
it: =E2=80=9CIt was very intense, it was awkward for everyone because it wa=
s <i>real</i>. This was not them being funny. This is the breakdown of a li=
felong friendship and relationship. And seeing it on public display from su=
ch people? It says so much about where the country is.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>In=
deed, as some of these folks reflected on the altercation, they also allude=
d to the way our polarized politics had affected their own once-cordial rel=
ations with fellow entrepreneurs and business leaders. =E2=80=9CThere are a=
 lot of people I know who were never political who have lost friends over t=
his,=E2=80=9D one executive said. =E2=80=9CThe idea that these two guys, wh=
o helped make each other, could lose their friendship over this=E2=80=A6 it=
=E2=80=99s sad.=E2=80=9D<br/></td>
         </tr>
